The paper discusses linear precoding for multi-antenna transmitters to serve multiple users, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The use of beamforming also suggests a possible category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses power constraints, which could fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI). The use of multicast and multigroup communication suggests a possible category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the optimization of beamforming weights, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
